commit.message: Removed some comments and destroying sqlite3 db on each test run.
Updated readme for new rake namespace.
Put integration tests in rake namespace.
Incremented version number for new behaviour.
Added trigger code to enforce not updating to invalid model type in Sqlite3 to match the behaviour in Postgresql. Added spec for the case.
Added test to ensure triggers are dropped properly.
Changed the sqlite3 trigger to reject unspecified models, just like postgres.
Decided to go with the explicit behaviour of non-specified models; will update sqlite3 adapter.
Changed the way the integration tests are run.
Added some more tests to ensure that destroy and delete both behave the same.
Added test to ensure that Fides doesn't interfere with dependent destroy.
Removed specific sqlite3 gem, incremented version.
Got SQLite3 tests working, was a class name conflict.
Figured out 90% of the SQLite3 integration tests config.
Added database.yml to igonre, change to example.
Added some integration tests for postgres, working on sqlite3.
Removed pry requirement, specified minitest version.
Added update constraint on poly table.
Renamed file to match module name.
Added pattern for using other adapters. Raising error if adapters don't work.
Raising ArgumentError in remove trigger method. Fixed error in example in docs.
Changed from class methods to instance methods for new migrations.
Added some tests and raising an exception for missing params on create.
Added test that Active record sees the methods.
Changed the name of a parameter.
Added caveat about only working with PostgreSQL at this time.
